This paper deals with a classic problem in distributed computing, specifically in the $\textsf{LOCAL}$ model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The problem of vertex coloring is a fundamental problem in graph theory, which falls under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Algorithmic Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses randomized and deterministic algorithms, which fall under the category of Randomized Algorithms (cs.AL) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
